main event: A round object was observed in Bremerton, Washington, on January 29, 1956, for a duration of 7 minutes.
interesting points: The object was described as the size of a pencil eraser and emitted a white light., The observation was ground-visual and there were three previous observations reported., The sighting coincided with three aircraft in the area., The observer was a warehouser at the navy yard named E.G.L. Vancil., The weather was noted as broken clouds with no snowfall.
sighted object: a round object emitting a white light
witness description: E.G.L. Vancil, a warehouser at the navy yard
